				<p><p>I think Chuck's answer is quite accurate. Just to add, there are two types of control loops. What Chuck has described is a <strong>closed control loop</strong>, and hence has a feedback loop to make sure the output is same as reference input or the set point. </p>

<p><strong>Open loop</strong>, on the other hand, doesn't need a feedback loop as the control action is independent of the process output.</p>
